Newcastle disease, Botswana
---------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 1 Aug 2014 from Dr Letlhogile Modisa, Director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, and Gaborone, Botswana

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Jan 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 17 Feb 2014
Report date: 1 Aug 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2011
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Virulent Newcastle disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, laboratory (advanced)

New outbreaks (5)
Outbreak 1: Serowe, Serowe, Serowe, Central
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Jan 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or dated resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 449 / 202 / 202 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Mainly backyard chickens

Outbreak 2: Mochudi, Mochudi, Mochudi, Kgatleng
Date of start of the outbreak: 10 Jan 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or dated resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 80 / 38 / 38 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Backyard chickens

Outbreak 3: Mogoditshane/Mmopane/Gaborone, Gaborone, Ramotswa, South East
Date of start of the outbreak: 17 Jan 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or dated resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 41 013 / 3212 / 349 / 0 / 0
Eurasian collared dove: _Streptopelia decaocto_ (Columbidae): 8 / 8 / 8 / 0 / 0

Outbreak 4: Kanye, Kanye, Kanye, Southern
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 Jan 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or dated resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 218 / 103 / 94 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Backyard chickens

Outbreak 5: Molepolole, Molepolole, Molepolole, Kweneng
Date of start of the outbreak: 13 Feb 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or dated resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 555 / 403 / 358 / 0 / 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 42 315 / 3958 / 1041 / 0 / 0
Eurasian collared dove: _Streptopelia decaocto_ (Columbidae): 8 / 8 / 8 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 9.35 percent / 2.46 percent / 26.30 percent / 2.46 percent
Eurasian collared dove: _Streptopelia decaocto_ (Columbidae): 100 percent / 100 percent / 100 percent / 100 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive; contact with wild species
Epidemiological comments: Several cases of Newcastle disease have been recorded in different districts with high morbidity and mortality. Epidemiological investigations are continuing and weekly updates will be given.

Control measures
Measures applied: No vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: Quarantine; movement control inside the country; vaccination in response to the outbreak (s); disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Botswana National Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory) / Birds / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 17 Feb 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

