[See important background information on Newcastle disease (ND) in the ProMED report, archive number 20140604.2517703.

The Eurasian collared dove (_Streptopelia decaocto_), most often simply called the collared dove, also sometimes hyphenated as Eurasian collared-dove, is a species of dove native to Asia and Europe, and also recently introduced in North America (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eurasian_collared_dove).

Photos of the Eurasian collared dove (_S. decaocto_) can be seen at http://tinyurl.com/odyna5u.

It is important for OIE member countries to remember that an "immediate notification" must be notified to the OIE within 24 hours of confirmation.

A map of Botswana's administrative divisions can be seen at http://www.ephotopix.com/image/africa/botswana_political_map.gif. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2654851,169.]
